   <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <!-- The marked up transcription goes here, surrounded by <ab> </ab> elements -->
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>χαῖρε καὶ πίε τένδι.
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="edition">
                <!-- The marked up transcription goes here, surrounded by <ab> </ab> elements -->
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>χαῖρε καῖ πί<surplus>ε</surplus>εἰ τένδι.
                </ab>  
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Typical formula for Little Master cups is χαῖρε καὶ πίει τένδε or τένδι. Herbert
                    transcribed the final word as εἰτένδι, describing it as Ionic.  This would be
                    highly unusual, however. A similar inscrption is attested on <hi rend="italic">CAVI</hi> 7025.</p>
            </div><div type="bibliography"> <xi:include href="http://library.brown.edu/usep_data/resources/titles.xml"> <xi:fallback> <p>US Ep bibliography</p> </xi:fallback> </xi:include> </div>

